        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Policy: add ingress channel conformance checks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds config-level Policy conformance checks for ingress/channel access. This is observability only: it reports whether `openclaw` config conforms to the operator policy file, and does not add runtime enforcement.\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"ingress\": {\n    \"session\": { \"requireDmScope\": \"per-channel-peer\" },\n    \"channels\": {\n      \"allowDmPolicies\": [\"pairing\", \"allowlist\", \"disabled\"],\n      \"denyOpenGroups\": true,\n      \"requireMentionInGroups\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nScope support:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"scopes\": {\n    \"telegram-ingress\": {\n      \"channelIds\": [\"telegram\"],\n      \"ingress\": {\n        \"channels\": {\n          \"allowDmPolicies\": [\"pairing\"],\n          \"denyOpenGroups\": true,\n          \"requireMentionInGroups\": true\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nNotes for reviewers:\n\n- `channelIds` scopes apply only to `ingress.channels.*`.\n- `ingress.session.requireDmScope` remains top-level/global because the session scope is not channel-attributable.\n- Evidence follows current runtime posture where known: omitted DM policy defaults to `pairing`; `dm.enabled=false` reports DM ingress as `disabled`; only supported `channels.defaults.groupPolicy` is inherited; configured `groups` imply allowlist posture; Slack-style `channels` entries do not imply allowlist posture; Telegram multi-account root groups are not inherited into named accounts; Feishu open groups default to no mention gate unless configured.\n- Nested `groupPolicy` is not treated as runtime enforcement. Nested `requireMention` is still observed where runtime uses it.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-85744-ingress-rebase node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=dot --testTimeout=30000` - 254 passed\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `node scripts/run-bundled-extension-oxlint.mjs`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/policy-state.ts && git diff --check`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md`\n- `~/.codex/skills/codex-review/scripts/codex-review --mode branch` - no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: config-level ingress conformance for DM scope, channel DM policy, open group posture, group mention gates, and `channelIds` scoped overlays.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 checkout under `/root/src/openclaw-policy-ingress-channel`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: focused policy Vitest wrapper, extensions typecheck, bundled-extension oxlint, oxfmt/diff check, docs MDX check, and Codex review as listed above.\n\nEvidence after fix: local proof passed after rebasing onto the updated sandbox policy branch; Codex review previously reported no discrete actionable correctness issues.\n\nObserved result after fix: policy doctor/CLI tests pass with 253 tests, and ingress evidence now mirrors the reviewed runtime posture edge cases.\n\nWhat was not tested: live channel message delivery was not exercised; this PR is config conformance only.\r\n\n",
